question_title: Will the community prediction be higher than 27.00% on 2026-02-14 for the Metaculus question "Will the United States experience negative GDP growth during Q1, Q2, or Q3 2026?"?
summary: This is a meta-prediction asking whether the Metaculus CP for US negative GDP growth will exceed 27% on Feb 14. The current CP is 29% (already 2pp above threshold) with 773 forecasters. For this to resolve NO, the CP would need to drop at least 2 percentage points in 9 days. With a large forecaster base providing stability, recent upward trend in CP (27%→29%), and no major economic data releases before resolution, the status quo favors YES. However, strong underlying economic fundamentals (4.2% Q4 GDP, 20-30% recession probability estimates) provide some downward pressure on recession expectations. The 2pp buffer is meaningful but not insurmountable if significant positive economic news emerges.

factors.description: Current CP is 29%, already 2pp above the 27% threshold - status quo resolves YES
Large forecaster base (773) provides stability - requires significant news to move CP substantially
Recent trend is upward (27%→29%), indicating current sentiment favors higher recession risk
No major GDP data release before Feb 14 - BEA advance estimate is Feb 20
Strong economic fundamentals (Q4 GDP 4.2%, most economists predict no recession) could push CP down
GDPNow update on Feb 10 could introduce new information shifting sentiment either direction
